57.5	Accra	Accra	Accra () is the capital and largest city of Ghana, with an urban population of 1,658,937 according to the 2000 census. Old Accra, comprising Jamestown and Usshertown, is also simply referred to by the locals as "Accra", which can be confusing to visitors. Accra is also the capital of the Greater Accra Region and of the Accra Metropolitan District, with which it is coterminous. Accra is furthermore the anchor of a larger metropolitan area, the Greater Accra Metropolitan Area (GAMA), which is home to about 4 million people, making it the largest metropolitan conglomeration in Ghana by population, and the eleventh-largest metropolitan area in Africa.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/af/Accra_montage.jpg/250px-Accra_montage.jpg
